---
/**
 * rest-api · 0008 · Figure 2 — "From shared secret to delegated identity"
 * (API key · Bearer token · OAuth 2.0 · OIDC).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson. Uses no arrow markers (plain <line>
 * connectors), so no <defs> is needed. See Fig1.astro for why figures are .astro
 * components rather than inline SVG.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 196"
        role="img"
        aria-label="API keys, bearer tokens, OAuth2 delegated authorization, and OIDC identity layer compared"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">FROM SHARED SECRET TO DELEGATED IDENTITY</text
            >
            <rect x="10" y="28" width="150" height="150" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="85" y="48" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700"
                >API key</text
            >
            <text x="85" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >shared secret in</text
            >
            <text x="85" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">a header</text>
            <text x="85" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >✓ simple svc-to-svc</text
            >
            <text x="85" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >✗ coarse, hard to rotate</text
            >
            <text x="85" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >✗ leaks easily</text
            >
            <text x="85" y="160" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >never in browser / URL</text
            >
            <rect x="166" y="28" width="150" height="150" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#6b675f"
            ></rect>
            <text x="241" y="48" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700"
                >Bearer token</text
            >
            <text x="241" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >Authorization:</text
            >
            <text x="241" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >Bearer &lt;token&gt;</text
            >
            <text x="241" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >"bearer is granted"</text
            >
            <text x="241" y="120" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >the token IS the</text
            >
            <text x="241" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >credential →</text
            >
            <text x="241" y="160" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >TLS + short life = all</text
            >
            <rect x="322" y="28" width="150" height="150" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="397"
                y="48"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">OAuth 2.0</text
            >
            <text x="397" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >delegated AUTHZ</text
            >
            <text x="397" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >user grants an app</text
            >
            <text x="397" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >scoped access — no</text
            >
            <text x="397" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >password shared</text
            >
            <text x="397" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >NOT authentication</text
            >
            <text x="397" y="160" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >on its own</text
            >
            <rect x="478" y="28" width="152" height="150" rx="9" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="554"
                y="48"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">OIDC</text
            >
            <text x="554" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >identity layer ON</text
            >
            <text x="554" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >TOP of OAuth2</text
            >
            <text x="554" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >adds id_token</text
            >
            <text x="554" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >(a JWT about you)</text
            >
            <text x="554" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >→ real AUTHENTICATION</text
            >
            <line x1="160" y1="103" x2="166" y2="103" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <line x1="316" y1="103" x2="322" y2="103" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <line x1="472" y1="103" x2="478" y2="103" stroke="#1f3a5a"></line>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Rule of thumb: <strong>OAuth2 = authorization; OIDC = authentication.</strong> Treating an OAuth
        access token as proof of identity is a classic senior gotcha.<sup
            ><a href="#s2" id="r2">2</a></sup
        ><sup><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
